verbs.description: misadd (third-person singular simple present misadds, present participle misadding, simple past and past participle misadded)

examples: And where a barrister, in summing up the items proved before him as arbitrator, misadded them, and thereby by mistake omitted 23l. in favour of the plaintiff, the Court, even at the instance of the barrister, would not allow an amendment, the defendant's counsel objecting.
